<plot>1941 in Bjelaja Zerkow near Kiew in Russia: a German special unit shoots 900 Jews, only 90 children are forgotten and survive. In two small rooms they vegetate packed like sardines, tarrying their fate. Two priests and general staff officer Groscurth report the terrible condition - but the consequences are even more terrible.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?146319</url></doc>
